ternal argument, whereas the latter impose event-structure sensitive perfectivity, which only induces the completion of a situation if the underlying eventuality denotes a simple change of state. An approach along these lines sheds light on the intricate properties of past participles and the auxiliaries they occur with, the determinants of auxiliary selection as well as the interplay of argument and event structure.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGermanic languagesxParticiple. 0aRomance languagesxParticiple. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Semantics.2bisacsh  aAuxiliary.  aPassive.  aPast Participle.  aPeriphrastic Perfect.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2019 Part 1z978311076246408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831106136670 cprintz978311061351340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311061614940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110616149423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110616149/original  a978-3-11-061030-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061685-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBoo